text: Sedgwick County (county code: SG) is a county located in the U.S. state of Kansas. In 2020, 523,824 lived there. This means that Sedgwick County has the 2nd most amount of people in Kansas. The county seat is Wichita, the biggest city in Kansas. ==Demographics== Sedgwick County is part of the Wichita, KS Metropolitan Statistical Area. ===Presidential elections=== Presidential election results Year Republican Democratic Third Parties 2020 54.4% 122,416 42.6% 95,870 2.9% 6,576 2016 54.4% 104,353 36.3% 69,627 9.3% 17,818 2012 58.2% 106,506 39.4% 71,977 2.4% 4,412 2008 55.2% 106,849 42.5% 82,337 2.4% 4,544 2004 62.1% 110,381 36.5% 64,839 1.4% 2,459 2000 57.4% 93,724 38.3% 62,561 4.4% 7,132 1996 56.1% 93,397 35.8% 59,643 8.1% 13,559 1992 40.5% 75,577 33.6% 62,670 25.9% 48,228 1988 55.3% 86,124 42.1% 65,618 2.6% 4,003 1984 62.5% 95,874 36.1% 55,263 1.4% 2,178 1980 51.8% 75,317 37.9% 55,105 10.3% 15,009 1976 50.7% 69,828 46.5% 63,989 2.8% 3,812 1972 65.7% 83,949 30.7% 39,220 3.6% 4,532 1968 51.8% 60,853 37.5% 44,041 10.7% 12,575 1964 43.8% 52,592 55.2% 66,372 1.0% 1,217 1960 55.2% 73,501 44.3% 58,887 0.5% 696 1956 61.1% 72,292 38.6% 45,732 0.3% 336 1952 66.5% 70,983 32.7% 34,926 0.8% 879 1948 49.6% 39,165 48.9% 38,621 1.6% 1,243 1944 52.8% 38,896 46.7% 34,442 0.5% 360 1940 48.1% 32,160 51.1% 34,219 0.8% 547 1936 35.3% 21,654 64.4% 39,503 0.3% 197 1932 41.5% 21,815 55.8% 29,344 2.7% 1,435 1928 74.4% 32,132 24.7% 10,649 0.9% 405 1924 57.2% 21,144 23.6% 8,712 19.2% 7,087 1920 59.2% 16,642 39.1% 10,998 1.8% 494 1916 41.8% 10,899 51.3% 13,391 6.9% 1,792 1912 9.8% 1,419 39.6% 5,752 50.6% 7,350 1908 50.3% 6,756 45.0% 6,049 4.8% 640 1904 60.8% 6,697 26.0% 2,869 13.2% 1,455 1900 50.0% 5,363 48.0% 5,144 2.0% 212 1896 42.7% 4,122 56.3% 5,434 1.1% 102 1892 46.7% 4,770 53.3% 5,448 1888 55.5% 6,071 36.8% 4,025 7.7% 841 Sedgwick County is somewhat conservative for an urban county.
